==Old English==
===Etymology===
West Germanic, from Germanic ''*tis-'', from Indo-European ''*dis''.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[ti-]], [[te-]], Old Saxon [[ti-]], Old High German [[zi-]], [[zir-]] (German [[zer-]]), Gothic [[𐌳𐌹𐍃-]], and with Latin [[dis-]].

